# Canonical MinaGuard verification-key hashes, one per network.
#
# NETWORK_DOMAIN is baked into the circuit as a compile-time constant
# (Field(1) for mainnet, Field(2) for testnet/devnet), so each network
# produces a structurally distinct VK. Cross-network proposal replay is
# therefore impossible at the proof level, not just application-level.
#
# Backend deployments: set MINAGUARD_VK_HASH to the hash for your target
# network (testnet hash for a testnet backend, mainnet hash for mainnet).
#
# Regenerate after any change under contracts/src:
#   bun run dev-helpers/cli.ts vk-hash compile
#   MINA_NETWORK_DOMAIN=mainnet bun run dev-helpers/cli.ts vk-hash compile
# Then update the two lines below with the printed hashes.
testnet=9864539027186763841869618029040137471378081021109346388628716514465982363557
mainnet=25935769953457180212736932792844424577725924087215649399581229887204057623621
